**Overall meaning:**

"May my mind be filled with auspicious resolve, the same resolve that carries men like swift horses in an excellent chariot, the same resolve that is unaging and powerful, residing in the heart."

**Explanation:**

This verse from the Upanishads utilizes a powerful metaphor to describe the power of the divine within. It compares this power to a chariot with swift horses, carrying men towards their destined goals. The image highlights the guiding and empowering nature of this force, enabling individuals to overcome obstacles and achieve their highest potential. The verse emphasizes the unaging and powerful nature of this force, which resides within the heart, waiting to be discovered and unleashed. 
